<p><strong>Overview</strong></p>
<p>
British Telecom is the largest telecommunications provider in the UK, and one of the largest communications providers globally, providing managed voice and data services to clients in over 150 countries globally. BT is undergoing a complete transformation. At the heart of this transformation is a $20 billion 21st century network (21CN) initiative. An IP-based, multi-service network, 21CN is the driver for a radical change in how consumers and business interact.
</p>
<p>
As part of this project, you are tasked with creating a mashup prototype application that integrates BT's ground-breaking network Web Services (code-named Web21C) with the raw power of Microsoft's Connected Services Framework (CSF) components.
</p>
<p>
Mashing together <a href="http://web21c.bt.com/">BT Services</a>, <a href="/">Microsoft CSF</a>, <a href="http://software.topcoder.com/catalog/index.jsp">TopCoder Components</a>, and third party Web services and content (as long as it is free and publicly available for commercial use), you can unleash your ideas, your curiosities, and your talents towards prototyping a usable mashup.
</p>
<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
Develop a prototype application based upon the winning submission from the BT Wireless Cities Mashup Design Competition. 
</p>

<ul>
<li>Your submission must include functionality from both the BT Wireless Cities and BT Business Mashup Design Competitions. Functionality for BT Business should be offered as a "service" for Wireless Cities.</li>
<li>See the Documentation section below for the BT Wireless Cities and BT Business specification documents.</li>
<li>The prototype mashup application must run within the <a href="http://www.networkmashups.com/">CSF Sandbox</a>.</li>
<li>Application entries must be your original work but based off of the BT Wireless Cites and BT Business mashup designs. The prototype must not infringe on the copyright or licenses of others.</li>
</ul>

