<h2>What are the BT Web Services?</h2>

<p>
The Web Services that are available enable designers and developers to access the power of BT's network to add powerful communications capabilities to applications:
</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Short Message Service</strong> - The Short Message Service (SMS) allows you to send SMS messages.</li>
<li><strong>Voice Call</strong> - The Voice Call service allows you to place phone calls from their application.</li>
<li><strong>Conference Call</strong> - The Conference Call service allows you to place and control conference calls.</li>
<li><strong>Presence</strong> - The Presence service allows you to store and retrieve an users' current status and availability for communication.</li>
<li><strong>Authentication</strong> - The Authentication service allows you to create and control an authentication realm for an application. This includes management and authentication of users.</li>
<li><strong>Information About Me</strong> - The Information About Me (IAM) service allows you to store and retrieve data about an individual in key value pairs.</li>
<li>More information about these services, along with examples, are listed here: <a href="http://web21c.bt.com">http://web21c.bt.com</a></li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Common Questions:</strong></p>

<ol>
<li><strong>What is a "Mashup"?</strong>
<br />A mashup is a hybrid Web application that has been combined from two or more Web services, and that provides an entirely different solution from either of the two disparate services.</li>
<li><strong>What is a "Managed Network Mashup"?</strong>
<br />Web services are combined with traditional telecommunications offerings, and then can be offered through the Software as a Service (SaaS) model and delivered across virtually any type of network or device.</li>
<li><strong>What is British Telecom (BT)?</strong>
<br />British Telecom (BT) is the largest telecommunications provider in the United Kingdom and one of the largest communications providers globally, providing managed voice and data services to clients in over 150 countries globally. BT is undergoing a complete 	transformation and at the heart of this change is a 21st century network initiative (21CN) 	costing nearly $20 billion. 21CN is an IP-based, multi-service network and will be the 	driver for radical change in the telecommunications industry.</li>
</ol>

